        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 17</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex017-P114r-L15_trl" n="15"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.002.016.trl.xml#Ex016-P114r-L15_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And all the congregation
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             of the children of Israel journeyed from the wilderness of Sin, after
                            their journeys,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             according to the commandment of the Lord, and dwelt in Rephidim. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             there was no water for the people to drink.</l>
                        <l n="2">And the people did strive
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             with Moses, and said, ‘Give us water that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             we may drink.’ And Moses said to them, ‘Why do you strive with me? Why
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             do you test the Lord?’</l>
                        <l n="3">And the people thirsted there
                            <milestone unit="page" n="114v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             for water, and the people murmured against Moses, and said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             ‘Why is this that you have brought us up from Egypt, to kill me and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             my children and my livestock with thirst?’</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             And Moses cried to the Lord, saying, ‘What shall I do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             to this people? A little time more and they will stone me with
                            stones.’</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             And the Lord said to Moses, ‘Pass before the people, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             take with you of the elders of Israel, and take your staff with which
                            you smote
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             the Nile in your hand, and go.</l>
                        <l n="6">Lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             my divine Presence stands before you there on the rock in Horeb,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and you shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             the people will drink.’ And Moses did so in the sight of the elders of
                            Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="7">And he called the name of the place Massah and Meribah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             because of the striving of the children of Israel, and because they
                            tested the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Lord, saying, ‘Is the providence of Lord among us
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             or not?’</l>
                        <l n="8">And Amalek came and fought with Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             in Rephidim.</l>
                        <l n="9">And Moses said to Joshua,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             ‘Choose men for us and go out, fight with Amalek.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             At daybreak, I will stand on the top of the rock with the staff
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             of God in my hand.’</l>
                        <l n="10">And Joshua did as Moses had said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             to him: he fought with Amalek. And Moses, Aaron, and Hur
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             went up to the top of the rock.</l>
                        <l n="11">And it was:
                            <milestone unit="page" n="115r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             when Moses lifted his hand, Israel prevailed; and when he lowered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             his hand, Amalek prevailed.</l>
                        <l n="12">And Moses’ hands were heavy.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             And they took a stone and put it under him, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             he sat on it. And Aaron and Hur held up his hands,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             one on this side and one on that side, and his hands were strong
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             until the sun went down.</l>
                        <l n="13">And Joshua slaughtered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             Amalek and his people with the edge of the sword. </l>
                        <l n="14">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             And the Lord said to Moses, ‘Write this in the book of memorial,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             and set it in the ears of Joshua, because I will certainly blot out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the remembrance of Amalek from under the skies.’</l>
                        <l n="15">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And Moses built an altar, and called the name of it <seg
                                type="commented" corresp="#Ex-017-seg001_trl" /><emph>The Lord
                                Nissi</emph><anchor type="commented" xml:id="Ex-017-seg001_trl"
                                 /><ref n="1" target="#Ex-017-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="16"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Ex-017-seg002_trl" />And he said,
                            ‘Because when there is a hand of a kingdom over the throne
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             of the kingdom of Israel, which is called the throne of God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             (which is an allegory of the kingdom of Shaul), then the war
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             of the Lord with Amalek will take place. And because Shaul did not do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             according to the Lord’s command to eradicate the memory of Amalek: for
                            that reason
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             every generation has the obligation to eradicate his memory, when the
                            time
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             of the rule of the kingdom of Israel comes.’<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Ex-017-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Ex-017-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
